pen catcher)}}\n{{MLBplayer|52|[[Carlos Febles]]}} {{small|(third base)}}\n{{MLBplayer|82|[[Tom Goodwin]]}} {{small|(first base/outfield)}}\n{{MLBplayer|51|[[Tim Hyers]]}} {{small|(hitting)}}\n{{MLBplayer|60|[[Dana LeVangie]]}} {{small|(pitching)}}\n{{MLBplayer|88|[[Mani Martinez]]}} {{small|(bullpen catcher)}}\n{{MLBplayer|10|[[Ron Roenicke]]}} {{small|(bench)}}\n{{MLBplayer|84|[[Ram\u00f3n V\u00e1zquez]]}} {{small|(coach)}}\n|}\n\n===MLB debuts===\nRed Sox players who made their MLB debuts during the 2018 regular season:\n* March 31: [[Bobby Poyner]]\n* April 1: [[Marcus Walden]]\n* June 7: [[Jalen Beeks]]\n\n===Transactions===\nNotable transactions of/for players on the 40-man roster during the 2018 regular season:\n* April 23: Pitcher [[Roenis El\u00edas]] was traded to the [[Seattle Mariners]] for cash or a [[Player to be named later|PTBNL]];<ref>{{cite web |url=http://m.redsox.mlb.com/roster/transactions/2018/04 |title=Red Sox Roster & Staff \u2013 Transactions |website=[[MLB.com]] |date=April 2018 |accessdate=May 25, 2018}}</ref> the Red Sox later received minor league OF/1B [https://www.baseball-reference.com/register/player.fcgi?id=filia-000eri Eric Filia];<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.boston.com/sports/boston-red-sox/2018/06/13/red-sox-mariners-trade-eric-filia |title=Red Sox receive minor leaguer to complete trade with Mariners |newspaper=[[The Boston Globe]] |date=June 13, 2018 |accessdate=June 13, 2018 |via=[[Boston.com]]}}</ref> however, he failed his physical and was returned to the Mariners, with cash considerations completing the trade.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.masslive.com/redsox/index.ssf/2018/06/boston_red_sox_return_eric_fil.html |title=Boston Red Sox return Eric Filia to Seattle Mariners after he didn't pass his physical |first=Christopher |last=Smith |website=masslive.com |date=June 15, 2018 |accessdate=June 16, 2018}}</ref>\n* May 25: First baseman [[Hanley Ram\u00edrez]] was [[designated for assignment]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/sports/redsox/2018/05/25/red-sox-part-ways-with-hanley-ramirez/V8PHkHq10EEMLEATQKCeQK/story.html|title=Red Sox to part ways with Hanley Ramirez|work=The Boston Globe|first=Alex|last=Speier|date=May 25, 2018|accessdate=May 25, 2018}}</ref><ref>https://twitter.com/RedSox/status/1000037175566766085</ref>\n* June 28: OF/1B [[Steve Pearce (baseball)|Steve Pearce]] was acquired from the [[Toronto Blue Jays]] for minor league infielder [https://www.baseball-reference.com/register/player.fcgi?id=espina000san Santiago Espinal].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mlb.com/news/red-sox-acquire-steve-pearce-from-blue-jays/c-283420492 |title=Red Sox acquire OF Pearce from Blue Jays |website=[[MLB.com]] |date=June 28, 2018 |accessdate=June 28, 2018}}</ref>\n* July 25: Pitcher [[Jalen Beeks]] was traded to the [[Tampa Bay Rays]] for pitcher [[Nathan Eovaldi]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.boston.com/sports/boston-red-sox/2018/07/25/red-sox-rays-nathan-eovaldi-trade |title=Red Sox acquire Nathan Eovaldi from Rays |first=Andrew |last=Mahoney |website=[[Boston.com]] |date=July 25, 2018 |accessdate=July 25, 2018}}</ref>\n* July 30: Second baseman [[Ian Kinsler]] was acquired from the [[Los Angeles Angels]] for Triple-A pitchers [[Ty Buttrey]] and [[Williams Jerez]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mlb.com/news/ian-kinsler-traded-to-red-sox/c-288130632 |title=With Pedroia's return uncertain, Sox get Kinsler |first=Ian |last=Browne |website=[[MLB.com]] |date=July 31, 2018 |accessdate=July 31, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Amateur draft===\nBoston's first 15 selections in the [[2018 Major League Baseball draft|2018 MLB draft]], held on June 4\u20136, are listed below.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://boston.redsox.mlb.com/team/draft.jsp?c_id=bos&year=2018 |title=Boston Red Sox 2018 Draft Selections |website=[[MLB.com]] |accessdate=June 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Round\n! scope=\"col\"| Pick\n! scope=