www.boston.com/sports/boston-red-sox/2018/11/27/dave-dombrowski-executive-of-the-year-red-sox-baseball-america |title=Dave Dombrowski was named Executive of the Year |first=Calli |last=Remillard |website=[[Boston.com]] |date=November 27, 2018 |accessdate=November 27, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sortname|J. D.|Martinez}}||[[Players Choice Awards]], Player of the Year|| rowspan=2|November 27, 2018 || rowspan=2|<ref>{{cite newspaper |url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/sports/redsox/2018/11/27/red-sox-martinez-mookie-betts-win-players-choice-awards/0aednXtwv1LO4NXlDmu5DM/story.html?p1=Article_Recirculation_Pos10 |title=Red Sox J.D. Martinez and Mookie Betts win Players Choice Awards |agency=[[Associated Press|AP]] |newspaper=[[The Boston Globe]] |url-access=limited |date=November 28, 2018 |accessdate=November 30, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Mookie|Betts}}||[[Players Choice Awards]], AL Outstanding Player\n|}\n* Alex Cora finished second to [[Bob Melvin]] of the [[Oakland Athletics]] for the AL [[Major League Baseball Manager of the Year Award|Manager of the Year Award]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://bbwaa.com/18-al-mgr/ |title=Bob Melvin joins select company by winning Manager of the Year for the 3rd time |website=[[Baseball Writers' Association of America|BBWAA]] |date=November 13, 2018 |accessdate=November 13, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Farm system==\n{{See also|Minor League Baseball}}\n\n{{MLB Farm System|level13=[[Triple-A (baseball)|AAA]]|team13=[[Pawtucket Red Sox]]|league13=[[International League]]|manager13=[[Kevin Boles]]\n|level14=[[Double-A (baseball)|AA]] |team14=[[Portland Sea Dogs]]|league14=[[Eastern League (baseball)|Eastern League]]|manager14=[https://www.baseball-reference.com/register/player.fcgi?id=fenste001dar Darren Fenster]\n|level15=[[Class A-Advanced|A-Advanced]] |team15=[[Salem Red Sox]]|league15=[[Carolina League]]|manager15=[[Joe Oliver (baseball)|Joe Oliver]]\n|level16=[[Single-A (baseball)|A]]|team16=[[Greenville Drive]]|league16=[[South Atlantic League]]|manager16=[https://www.baseball-reference.com/register/player.fcgi?id=suarez001ign Iggy Suarez]\n|level17=[[Class A-Short Season|A-Short Season]]|team17=[[Lowell Spinners]]|league17=[[New York\u2013Penn League]]|manager17=[[Corey Wimberly]]\n|level18=[[Rookie League|Rookie]]|team18=[[Gulf Coast League Red Sox|GCL Red Sox]]|league18=[[Gulf Coast League]]|manager18=[[Tom Kotchman]]\n|level19=[[Rookie League|Rookie]]|team19=[[Dominican Summer League Red Sox|DSL Red Sox 1]]|league19=[[Dominican Summer League]]|manager19=[[Aly Gonz\u00e1lez]]\n|level20=[[Rookie League|Rookie]]|team20=[[Dominican Summer League Red Sox|DSL Red Sox 2]]|league20=[[Dominican Summer League]]|manager20=[[Fernando Tat\u00eds]]\n}}\n\n== Allegations of electronic sign stealing ==\nOn January 7, 2020, ''[[The Athletic]]'' published a report alleging that the Red Sox broke MLB rules by using a video replay room during 2018 regular season games to decipher the signs of opposing catchers, according to three unnamed sources who were with the team that year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theathletic.com/1510673/2020/01/07/mlbs-sign-stealing-controversy-broadens-sources-say-the-red-sox-used-video-replay-room-illegally-in-2018/|title=MLB's sign-stealing controversy broadens: Sources say the Red Sox used video replay room illegally in 2018|last=Drellich|first=Ken Rosenthal and Evan|website=The Athletic|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> This news broke while the league was already investigating the Houston Astros for also allegedly stealing signs electronically during their [[2017 Houston Astros season|2017 season]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theathletic.com/1363451/2019/11/12/the-astros-stole-signs-electronically-in-2017-part-of-a-much-broader-issue-for-major-league-baseball/|title=The Astros stole signs electronically in 2017 \u2014 part of a...|last=Drellich|first=Ken Rosenthal and Evan|website=The Athletic|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> Alex Cora, who managed the Red Sox in 2018, had served as bench coach for the Astros in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bostonherald.com/2020/01/07/alex-coras-reputation-at-stake-in-red-sox-sign-stealing-scandal/|title=Alex Cora\u2019s reputation at stake in Red Sox\u2019 sign-stealing scandal|date=2020-01-08|website=Boston Herald|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> MLB launched an investigation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thescore.com/mlb/news/1922282|title=Report: Red Sox used replay room to illegally steal signs in 2018|last=Mcwilliam|first=Bryan|website=theScore.com|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref>\n\nThis was not the first time the Red Sox were investigated for alleged electronic sign stealing. During the [[2017 Boston Red Sox season|2017 season]], they were fined by MLB for using an [[Apple Watch]] to relay stolen signs to hitters in games against the New York Yankees.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/espn/wire/_/section/mlb/id/20594369|title=Report: Red Sox used Apple Watch to steal Yankees' signs|website=ESPN.com|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> On September 15, 2017, commissioner [[Rob Manfred]] had said in regards to the investigation into Boston's illicit use of an Apple Watch: \"I have received absolute assurances from the Red Sox that there will be no future violations of this type.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbssports.com/mlb/news/mlb-rules-on-red-sox-yankees-sign-stealing-and-fines-both-teams/|title=MLB rules on Red Sox-Yankees sign stealing and fines both teams|website=CBSSports.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/JeffPassan/status/1214677058414161921?s=09|title=Rob Manfred on Sept. 15, 2017 regarding the investigation into Boston's illicit use of an Apple Watch: \"I have received absolute assurances from the Red Sox that there will be no future violations of this type.\" This undoubtedly will factor into any potential discipline for Sox.|last=Passan|first=Jeff|date=2020-01-07|website=@JeffPassan|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref>\n\nOn April 22, 2020, commissioner [[Rob Manfred]] issued his report from the investigation,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mlb.com/news/red-sox-sign-stealing-decision |title=Commissioner decision on Red Sox investigation |website=[[MLB.com]] |date=April 22, 2020 |accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref> determining that the Red Sox replay operator had \"utilized the game feeds in the replay room\" to decode sign sequences but those actions were \"limited in scope and impact\", as the decoding only happened during some occurrences of the opposing team having a runner on second base and were not known to the manager, the  coaching staff, the front office, or most of the players.\" The video replay operator was suspended for the 2020 season (including postseason) and the team forfeited their second-round selection in the [[2020 Major League Baseball draft|2020 MLB draft]]. Cora was separately suspended for a year for his actions in the Houston situation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/mlb/story/_/id/29083660/mlb-suspends-red-sox-replay-operator-1-year-docks-draft-pick-punishment-sign-stealing-scandal|title=MLB suspends Red Sox replay operator, docks draft pick; Alex Cora suspended for conduct with Astros|work=ESPN.com|date=April 22, 2020|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Boston Red Sox team records]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite news |url=https://www.boston.com/sports/boston-red-sox/2018/10/31/red-sox-parade-live-updates |title=A moment-by-moment recap of the Red Sox victory parade |first=Hayden |last=Bird |website=[[Boston.com]] |date=October 31, 2018 |accessdate=October 31, 2018}}\n* {{cite news |url=https://www.mlb.com/redsox/news/see-the-red-sox-players-weekend-nicknames/c-289581714 |title=See the Red Sox Players' Weekend nicknames |first=Ian |last=Browne |website=[[MLB.com]] |date=August 9, 2018 |accessdate=August 13, 2018}}\n* {{cite news |url=https://www.boston.com/sports/boston-red-sox/2018/09/25/red-sox-franchise-record-106-wins-chad-finn |title=Let\u2019s pause and appreciate what we\u2019ve seen from these magical Red Sox |first=Chad |last=Finn |website=[[Boston.com]] |date=September 25, 2018 |accessdate=September 26, 2018}}\n* {{cite news |url=https://www.boston.com/sports/boston-red-sox/2018/10/29/red-sox-world-series-teams-ranked |title=Where does this Red Sox championship rank among the four this century? |first=Chad |last=Finn |website=[[Boston.com]] |date=October 29, 2018 |accessdate=October 29, 2018}}\n* {{cite news |url=https://www.boston.com/sports/boston-red-sox/2019/04/09/red-sox-world-series-rings |title=Here are the Red Sox\u2019 2018 World Series rings |first=Tommy |last=McArdle |website=[[Boston.com]] |date=April 9, 2019 |accessdate=April 9, 2019}}\n* {{cite news |url=http://www.espn.com/mlb/story/_/id/24259760/mlb-the-best-boston-red-sox-team-ever |title=This just might be the best Red Sox team ... ever |first=David |last=Schoenfield |website=[[ESPN]] |date=August 3, 2018 |accessdate=August 5, 2018}}\n* {{cite web |url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefings-statements/remarks-president-trump-welcoming-2018-world-series-champions-boston-red-sox/ |title=Remarks by President Trump Welcoming the 2018 World Series Champions Boston Red Sox |website=whitehouse.gov |date=May 9, 2019 |accessdate=May 10, 2019}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://boston.redsox.mlb.com/schedule/sortable.jsp?c_id=bos&year=2018 2018 Boston Red Sox season at Official Site]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20180408074048/http://pressroom.redsox.com/GetFile.ashx?&Location=MEDIA%20GUIDE%2FMedia%20Guides%2F2018%20Boston%20Red%20Sox%20Media%20Guide.pdf 2018 Boston Red Sox Media Guide]\n\n{{World Series champions}}\n{{American League champions}}\n{{American League East champions}}\n{{2018 MLB Playoffs navbox}}\n{{2018 MLB season by team}}\n{{2018 Boston Red Sox}}\n{{Boston Red Sox}}\n\n[[Category:2018 in sports in Massachusetts|Boston Red Sox]]\n[[Category:2018 Major League Bas